# API Routes

1. Always `await connectDB()` from `@/app/utils/database` before queries
2. Import the matching Mongoose model from `@/app/models/`
3. GET → `request.nextUrl.searchParams`; POST → `await request.json()`
4. Return `NextResponse.json(data)`

POST body convention:

```typescript
const { params } = await request.json();
const { level, study } = params || {};
```

*Today endpoints:

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `class/route.ts` | GET — metadata (levels) |
| `study/route.ts` | GET — study units |
| `list/route.ts` | POST — `$sample` random (free) |
| `listAll/route.ts` | POST — full sorted list (paid) |

Reference: `src/app/api/grammarToday/list/route.ts`
